<TITLE> BCB serves notice on CEO on unapproved leave </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 23 (bdnews24.com)The Bangladesh Cricket Board has served notice on its chief executive officer Mahmudur Rahman, asking for an explanation for his taking leave without permission. "We have served a showcause notice on him (Rahman), asking him to explain why he had visited Europe without leave granted," BCB president M Abdul Aziz told bdnews24.com Monday. "We have also asked for other information from him, relating to his responsibilities, which will become public after submission of his reply to the notice," said Aziz, who is also agricultural secretary. The cricket board's CEO Mahmudur Rahman sought holiday leave to visit other parts of Europe after attending the International Cricket Council meeting in London last month. However, the BCB denied his leave summoning him to attend a board meeting in Dhaka on July 30. Nevertheless, after attending the board meeting, Rahman left Bangladesh for Europe the next day without the board's permission. bdnews24.
